Package wtf.file.api.editable.compression

Enum-Klasse DataCompressionType

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<DataCompressionType>
wtf.file.api.editable.compression.DataCompressionType
Alle implementierten Schnittstellen:
Serializable, Comparable<DataCompressionType>, Constable
public enum DataCompressionType extends Enum<DataCompressionType>
Enum representing the types of data compression available for use in image saving operations. Each compression type determines whether specific compression techniques, such as CLUT coding or Reference-based compression, are used.

The following data compression types are available: - NO_COMPRESSION: No data compression is applied. - INLINE_COMPRESSION: Only reference-based compression is applied. - MAPPED_COMPRESSION: Only CLUT-based compression is applied. - COMBINED_COMPRESSION: Both CLUT and reference-based compression techniques are applied.

The compression type can be used to optimize data storage and performance during save operations and other data processing tasks.
